rules.query:
Collect the labeled total rows and major subtotal captions from each primary financial statement (Balance Sheet, Statement of Operations, Statement of Changes in Partners' Capital, Statement of Cash Flows, and Schedule of Investments when present). Flag instances where the same numeric total or the same caption text appears on multiple statements WITHOUT a legitimate cross-statement basis.

Legitimate (do NOT flag) cases include the documented tie-outs covered by other rules:
  - ending cash repeated on BS and SCF;
  - ending Partners'/Members' Capital repeated on BS and CHG;
  - net increase from operations repeated on OPS, CHG, and SCF;
  - SOI total fair value repeated as the BS investments line.

Flag (suspected copy/paste) cases include the same large number appearing on two statements where no tie-out relationship exists, or the same line caption appearing in two statements where it does not belong (e.g., 'Total expenses' duplicated onto the Balance Sheet). Normalize numbers: remove '$', commas; treat parentheses as negative.

Pass criteria: All repeated totals/captions across statements are explained by a legitimate tie-out or shared subtotal.

Fail criteria: A total or caption repeats across statements with no tie-out basis.

needs_review when the relationship is plausible but not clearly one of the listed tie-outs.
